cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.IR

This paper deals with the application of data mining techniques to predict lung cancer survivability from patient records. The paper discusses the use of two classification techniques, J48 implementation of the C4.5 algorithm and Naive Bayes classifier. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the application of machine learning techniques to solve real-world problems. The paper also involves data pre-processing activities, which makes cs.DB (Databases) another likely sub-category. The use of classification techniques also falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of patient records, which can be considered as a form of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category.
